<!DOCTYPE ui:UiBinder SYSTEM "http://dl.google.com/gwt/DTD/xhtml.ent">
<ui:UiBinder xmlns:ui="urn:ui:com.google.gwt.uibinder"
             xmlns:g="urn:import:com.google.gwt.user.client.ui">
    <ui:with type="fr.lteconsulting.hexa.client.css.bindings.SkeletonHexaCss"
             field="s"></ui:with>
    <ui:with type="fr.lteconsulting.hexacss.client.Css" field="css"></ui:with>
    <g:ScrollPanel>
        <g:HTMLPanel>
            <div class="{s.container}">
                <h1>Sample GWT app with Skeleton used through HexaCss</h1>

                <hr/>

                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.oneHalfColumn} {s.column}">
                        <h4>Stop coding non-responsive applications. Let users use your applications from anywhere.</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="{s.oneHalfColumn} {s.column}">
                        Those are standards GWT buttons. The first one has absolutely no style added :
                        <pre>
                            <code>Button b = new Button();</code>
                        </pre>
                        <g:Button ui:field="button1">Normal</g:Button>
                        <g:Button ui:field="button2" stylePrimaryName="{s.buttonPrimary}">Primary</g:Button>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr/>

                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.twelveColumns}">
                        <h4>Intro</h4>
                        <p>
                            <a target="_blank" href="http://getskeleton.com/">Skeleton</a>
                            is a dead simple, responsive CSS boilerplate.
                            It has the very basic minimum to start a application, with full responsiveness. So why not
                            base our new
                            <a target="_blank" href="http://www.gwtproject.org/">GWT</a>
                            applications
                            on it ? With<a target="_blank" href="www.lteconsulting.fr/hexacss">HexaCss</a>, using
                            Skeleton is really easy and type-safe. For example,
                            in the Java code and UiBinder, you get the class names auto-completion !
                        </p>

                        <p>Look at the
                            <a target="_blank"
                               href="https://github.com/ltearno/hexa.tools/tree/master/hexa.css/samples/sample5">code
                            </a>
                            of this sample to
                            get an idea on how to use it. It's very simple, just like the usual CssResource.
                        </p>

                        <p>One of the cool things with Skeleton is that it applies styles on HTML elements, so you can
                            use most if the time use GWT widgets
                            out-of-the-box, they will be already styled.
                        </p>

                        <p>Here are some samples of the GWT / Skeleton / HexaCss possibilities :</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr/>

                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <h4>The Grid</h4>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.twelveColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Twelve</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.oneColumn} {css.exampleColumn}">One</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.elevenColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Eleven</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.twoColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Two</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.tenColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Ten</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.threeColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Three</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.nineColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Nine</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.fourColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Four</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.eightColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Eight</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.fiveColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Five</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.sevenColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Seven</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.sixColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Six</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.sixColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Six</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.sevenColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Seven</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.fiveColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Five</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.eightColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Eight</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.fourColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Four</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.nineColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Nine</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.threeColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Three</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.tenColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Ten</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.twoColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Two</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.elevenColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Eleven</div>
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.oneColumn} {css.exampleColumn}">One</div>
                </div>
                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.twelveColumns} {css.exampleColumn}">Twelve</div>
                </div>

                <hr/>

                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.twelveColumns}">
                        <h4>Forms</h4>
                        <p>This is a form with standard GWT widgets :</p>
                        <form>
                            <div class="{s.row}">
                                <div class="{s.sixColumns} {s.columns}">
                                    <label for="exampleEmailInput">Your email</label>
                                    <g:TextBox ui:field="textbox" styleName="{s.uFullWidth}"></g:TextBox>
                                </div>
                                <div class="{s.sixColumns} {s.columns}">
                                    <label for="exampleRecipientInput">Reason for contacting</label>
                                    <g:ListBox ui:field="listbox" styleName="{s.uFullWidth}"></g:ListBox>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <label for="exampleMessage">Message</label>
                            <g:TextArea ui:field="textarea" styleName="{s.uFullWidth}"></g:TextArea>

                            <label class="{s.uPullRight}">
                                <g:CheckBox ui:field="checkbox">Send a copy to yourself</g:CheckBox>
                            </label>

                            <g:SubmitButton ui:field="submit" styleName="{s.buttonPrimary}">Submit</g:SubmitButton>
                        </form>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr/>

                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.twelveColumns}">
                        <h4>Tables</h4>
                        <g:FlexTable ui:field="table" styleName="{s.uFullWidth}"></g:FlexTable>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr/>

                <div class="{s.row}">
                    <div class="{s.column} {s.twelveColumns}">
                        <h4>Outro</h4>
                        <p>You can find the HexaCss project here :<a target="_blank"
                                                                     href="www.lteconsulting.fr/hexacss">
                            www.lteconsulting.fr/hexacss</a>, which
                            was made with love by Arnaud Tournier @<a target="_blank" href="www.lteconsulting.fr">LTE
                                Consulting</a>.
                        </p>

                        <p>The Skeleton project is<a target="_blank" href="http://getskeleton.com/">here</a>.
                        </p>

                        <p>And the GitHub repo containing HexaCss and many other things can be found<a target="_blank"
                                                                                                       href="https://github.com/ltearno/hexa.tools">
                            here</a>.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </g:HTMLPanel>
    </g:ScrollPanel>
</ui:UiBinder> 